---
title: Identity Registry — Kademlia DHT Lookup
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant LC as Local Cache
    participant N1 as DHT Node 1\n(closest known)
    participant N2 as DHT Node 2
    participant N3 as DHT Node 3\n(key holder)
    participant IR as Identity Record

    C->>LC: Lookup SHA-256("bob@example.com")

    alt Cache hit — key fresh
        LC-->>C: Bob's identity_record ✓
        Note over C,LC: Typical case for known contacts\nCache hit rate 90%+ for established users
    else Cache miss or stale
        LC-->>C: Not found / expired

        Note over C,N1: DHT routes by XOR distance\nO(log N) hops to converge
        C->>N1: FIND_NODE SHA-256("bob@example.com")
        N1-->>C: Closer nodes: [N2, N4, N5]

        C->>N2: FIND_NODE SHA-256("bob@example.com")
        N2-->>C: Closer nodes: [N3, N6]

        C->>N3: FIND_VALUE SHA-256("bob@example.com")
        N3->>IR: Retrieve identity_record
        IR-->>N3: identity_record

        Note over N3: Verify self_signature on record\nbefore returning
        N3-->>C: identity_record (verified ✓)

        Note over C: Verify self_signature independently
        C->>LC: Cache identity_record + pubkeys

        Note over C: For multi-device recipients:\nreturns primary key + all\nactive device_subkey_records
        C-->>C: Encrypt CEK for each\nactive device sub-key
    end

    Note over C,N3: Registry nodes never learn\nwhat message is being sent\nOnly that a lookup occurred
